  "prompt": "What was Jesus like as a child?",
  "response": "The Bible provides very limited information about Jesus' childhood. The Gospels of Matthew and Luke mention a few details:\n\n1. He was born in Bethlehem to Mary and Joseph.\n\n2. His early years included escaping to Egypt to avoid King Herod's persecution, then returning to Nazareth.\n\n3. At age 12, he was found in the temple discussing religious teachings with scholars, amazing them with his understanding. When his parents found him, he said he needed to be about his \"Father's business\" (Luke 2:41-52).\n\n4. He is described as growing in wisdom and stature, and in favor with God and people.\n\nBeyond these brief accounts, the Bible does not provide detailed descriptions of Jesus' childhood. Most of the biblical narrative focuses on his adult ministry, crucifixion, and resurrection.\n\nSome non-biblical traditions and legends exist about Jesus' childhood, but these are not considered historically reliable by scholars. The canonical gospels intentionally focus more on his adult life and mission.",
